item.description:
arXiv:2403.15211v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: In this article, we study the growth of solutions of the homogeneous complex linear differential equation \begin{equation*}
  f^{(k)}+A_{k-1}(z)f^{(k-1)}+\cdots+A_{1}(z)f^{\prime}+ A_{0}(z)f=0, \end{equation*}% where the coefficients $A_{j}(z)$ $(j=0,1,\ldots ,k-1)$ are analytic or meromorphic functions in $\overline{\mathbb{C}}\setminus\{z_{0}\}$. Under the sufficient condition that there exists one dominant coefficient by its logarithmic lower order or by its logarithmic lower type. We extend some precedent results due to Liu, Long and Zeng and others.
